headline: TE Connectivity (TEL) Is Up 5.9% After AI Revenue Surges And $750 Million Refi - Has The Bull Case Changed?
summary: In early February 2026, TE Connectivity, through Tyco Electronics Group S.A., priced a US$750 million senior notes offering, intending to use roughly US$745.5 million of proceeds to refinance 2026 debt maturities and fund general corporate purposes, while also highlighting broadening demand across AI, grid hardening, and next-generation vehicles.
